{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_17","type":"reasoning","text":"**Evaluating error handling and UI aspects**\n\nI'm thinking about some potential errors and UI improvements. For instance, if there's an error, I need to reset idle and toast notifications. Also, `toast.success` and `toast.error` might still trigger after unmount, so I should guard against that. \n\nThen there's `userData.full_name`, which could be absent, and `userData.partner` might be zero or an empty string, affecting fetch checks. If `partnerName` starts as null, if the fetch returns an empty string, the display might fall back to no restaurant. \n\nI also noticed the `Input` component is missing `aria-label`, and I should add labels. The readonly email input could need to be disabled or marked as `aria-readonly` because on mobile, it can still focus and show the keyboard, though it usually doesn't on iOS."}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_18","type":"reasoning","text":"**Identifying UI issues**\n\nI'm noting several UI issues that need addressing. The save button has a minimum height, but input fields are missing that feature, which IО“ГҮГ–ve already marked in the BUGS list. \n\nAdditionally, full screen containers in PartnerShell need the same minimum height, and decorative icons are lacking `aria-hidden` attributes. The back button in the header is fine since it has included text, but the error container should have a role alert.\n\nI'm also catching an issue with a `tr` wrapper where the fallback returns undefined and double-checking the PartnerShell import alias path has been resolved. Lastly, the console's comment encoding appears garbled, likely due to output encoding, but it's probably not a critical issue."}}
